Former Ekiti state governor, Ayo Fayose, has spoken on speculations about his well-being. Fayose allegedly has some health issues which has kept him away from the public scene. On Wednesday, Fayose via his Twitter account said he only underwent a medical check up. He debunked suggestions that he was admitted to a hospital. He tweeted: “These “hailers”, when I was on their case, they were crying. Now I’m on my own lane enjoying my life, they are still crying & sulking. “Expect more so you can cry more. I’m on medical check up not admission. “Celebrating New Year is my right, haters can hug transformer. Happy New Year”